abstract: Kenyan javelin thrower Julius Yego wins first world championships gold medal in field event for country at tournament in Beijing; victory comes same day that two Kenyan runners are suspended for doping.
lead_paragraph: The javelin thrower Julius Yego won the first world championships gold medal in a field event for Kenya, a country known for distance running.
